To send a device to an Aux, first click the '''Output''' icon to open the mixer (image below) then click the '''Aux''' button in the lower right of the module (image below).
This will open a panel of aux sliders (1-4) that send the signal. Choose the Aux you want to send to and move up its respective slider.


[[File:Kontakt aux module sliders.png]]




You need to make sure the outputs of the '''Aux''' is set in a manner that it can be heard. Click '''Conf''' at the bottom of the '''Aux''' channel strip and in the window that appears left-click the output assignment (image below) and choose outputs that can be heard.



